the heart of ezra greer is a 1917 american silent drama film produced by the thanhouser company and directed by emile chautard .   the film focuses on ezra greer , a successful middle-aged man who searches for his college age daughter , mary .   the wayward mary was romanced and abandoned by jack denbeigh , later bearing his child .   once ezra becomes broke he finds employment as the valet for jack denbeigh .   after jack 's engagement to a cabaret girl , mary becomes upset and leaves her child at jack 's home .   contrary to jack 's wishes , ezra keeps the child and jack ultimately reveals that the child is his own .   ezra convinces jack to make things right and ezra convinces the cabaret girl to leave jack .   after a carriage accident in which the baby is injured , ezra and jack rush to the hospital and find mary as a nurse crying over the child .   the film ends with the marriage of jack and mary .   the film was released by path√© on october 7 , 1917 .   the film was the final release from thanhouser and was deemed to be an average film by most reviewers .   criticism for the film hinged on far-fetched coincidences to drive the plot . the film is presumed lost .